Sentencas: Herein, we report a phase-transformed fuel electrode to carry out the reversible CO-CO2 conversion in a reversible solid oxide electrochemical cell (RSOC), which is composed of self-assembled FeRu bimetallic nanoparticles and Ruddlesden-Popper Pr0.8Sr1.2Fe1-x-yRuxMoyO4 (FeRu@PSFRM).
Titulo: Self-assembled FeRu bimetallic nanocatalysts for efficient and durable mutual CO-CO2 conversion in a reversible solid oxide electrochemical cell

Sentencas: The single cell with the FeRu@PSFRM fuel electrode generates a maximum output power density of 170 W cm(-2) at 800 degrees C in the solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) mode, while yields a current density of -0.256 A cm(-2) at 1.3 V in the solid oxide electrolysis cell (SOEC) mode.
Titulo: Self-assembled FeRu bimetallic nanocatalysts for efficient and durable mutual CO-CO2 conversion in a reversible solid oxide electrochemical cell

Sentencas: In addition, the reliable reversible CO-CO2 mutual conversion has experienced activation-stabilization-degradation three obvious stages in the first 42-h SOFC-SOEC cycling testing.

Titulo: Self-assembled FeRu bimetallic nanocatalysts for efficient and durable mutual CO-CO2 conversion in a reversible solid oxide electrochemical cell

Sentencas: Our findings reveal that the FeRu@PSFRM material generated by the in-situ exsolution technique is a promising fuel electrode candidate for efficient and durable mutual CO-CO2 conversion in a RSOC.
